            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-12-24T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-12-24T17:00:00-05:00" n="566" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d566">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.936/12–2448: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-12-24T17:00:00-05:00">December 24, 1948—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1882. Mme Chiang has informed Secretary she has recd word from Gimo that Amb has
                    indicated desirability ChiGovt entering into peace negotiations with Comms. She
                    also indicates Philip Fugh may have had some connection this matter.</p>
                <p>As stated Deptel 1852 Dec 17 Dept considers coalition govt China strictly Chi
                    responsibility and desires no responsibility whatsoever be attributed this Govt
                    for formation, composition, or basis such govt. This tel also stated Emb should
                    participate in no way either formally or otherwise in discussions or maneuvers
                    leading thereto <pb facs="0692" n="682" xml:id="pg_682"/> and that this
                    represented reiteration US Govt position reviewed previous related
                    communications.</p>
                <p>You should take steps ensure no member Emb staff or anyone connected with Emb
                    participates any action contrary sense foregoing instructions which could be
                    interpreted as indication or implication this Govt encouraging or suggesting
                    ChiGovt negotiations with Comms.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
